text: Peter John Squires (born 1936), is a male former diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== He represented Great Britain in the Diving at the 1960 Summer Olympics. He represented England in the 3 metres springboard at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. He was associated to the Highgate Diving Club. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:English male divers Category:Divers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Divers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Living people
